description:
The upcoming Ryzen Z2 GO may be essentially a 4-core version of the Ryzen 6800U.

In this video, we explore the potential performance of the Legion GO S by using a handheld powered by an AMD Ryzen 6800U with only 4 active CPU cores. Recent Legion GO S benchmarks suggest remarkably similar performance, hinting at this possibility. Once we acquire the GO S, we will conduct a thorough comparison to verify these findings
